cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with image retrieval using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) trained on brain MRI scans with heterogeneous labels. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses multitask learning to train the CNN, which involves optimizing multiple objectives simultaneously, and this falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of relevant information about tumors, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves retrieving relevant images based on their similarity to a query image.
